                                                 java.lang.String functor,

        If rule 'ruleName' was been triggered, a conclusion matching 'DRLConclusion' pattern would be achieved
        Parameters:
        ruleName - Rule name of a rule that could get DRLConclusion
        functor - Object/fact type of the expected conclusion
        DRLConclusion - String with expected conclusion in drl format
        Returns:
        Return true if a conclusion from rule's RHS would match 'DRLConclusion' pattern (condition): this means that if rule ruleName had been fired, the conclusion DRLConclusion would have been achieved.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - If a query to evaluate a condition is not defined
